    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix invalid memory access in nr_pusch_codeword_scrambling_uci function\n\n### Summary\nThe `nr_pusch_codeword_scrambling_uci` function in the NR ULSCH processing module contained a critical bug that caused segmentation faults when processing UCI placeholder bits. When the function encountered an `NR_PUSCH_y` placeholder at the beginning of a 32-bit output word, it attempted to access `*(out-1)`, which pointed to memory before the allocated buffer.\n\nThis issue occurred during PUSCH transmission when UCI data was being scrambled, specifically when the first bit of a new 32-bit word in the output buffer was an `NR_PUSCH_y` placeholder. The invalid memory access caused immediate termination of the process with a segmentation fault.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/NR_UE_TRANSPORT/nr_ulsch_ue.c`: Replaced invalid memory access with proper tracking of previous bit value using a local variable. Added initialization of `prev_bit` to 0 and updated it after each bit processing. Modified the `NR_PUSCH_y` handling to copy the previous bit value instead of accessing invalid memory.\n"
}